  "notes": "Reused high-count existing tags as canonical where good: `how-igor-ticks` (45, collapsed casing variant), `emotional-intelligence` (43, absorbs \"emotion\"/\"emotional-health\"/\"emotional-resilience\"), `book-notes` (33, absorbs \"book-summary\"/\"book-recommendations\"/the \"heath\" typo which clearly meant Heath Brothers but I folded it into book-notes since it tagged a book summary), `ai` (26), `physical-health` (absorbs \"fitness\"/\"sleep\"/\"hiit\" etc), `manager` (9), `job-hunt` (3), `weight-loss` (2).\n\nHard placements / judgment calls:\n- \"heath\" typo: ambiguous — could be \"health\" or \"Heath Brothers\" (referenced in /nurture and /death book summaries). Given both its likely sources are book summaries, I folded it into `book-notes`, NOT `health`. Flagging because the prompt suggested it collapses to \"health\" — but context (Heath Brothers) argues otherwise. If you want it under health instead, move it to `physical-health`/`emotional-intelligence`.\n- `spiritual` vs `mortality` vs `death`: /death legitimately spans all three. Kept `mortality` as the broad reflective tag (also on /weeks) and `death` as the narrow topical one; `spiritual-health` collapsed into `spiritual`.\n- `evals` vs `ai-tooling`: /hill-climbing is really about building evals/fitness functions for agent loops. Made `evals` its own canonical tag (absorbing optimization/hill-climbing/model-as-judge/TDD) rather than burying it under ai-tooling.\n- `mental-health` vs `emotional-intelligence`: these overlap heavily. I scoped `mental-health` to clinical/disordered states (depression, anxiety, impostor-syndrome) and `emotional-intelligence` to skill/relational EQ. /depression and /interviewsarehard get both where warranted.\n- `software-engineering` is doing double duty for /software-rot (maintenance/bit-rot) and the engineering side of /adblocker-trojan and /hill-climbing. Considered a separate `technical-debt` tag but YAGNI — it would only land on one post.\n- `productivity` (existing count 6) is the closest home for the \"effective workflow\" angle in /viz, /advertising, /covid, /weeks — slightly broad but reused rather than inventing `personal-productivity`.\n- Dropped over-broad junk candidates from the source tags: \"tools\", \"tech\", \"meta\", \"navigation\", \"current-events\" (folded into media-criticism), \"mindset\" (folded into decision-making/stoicism), \"perspective\" (folded into stoicism). \"search-featured\"/\"blog-meta\"/\"explainer\" from the existing vocab are site-mechanics tags, not topical, so excluded from the canonical topic vocabulary.\n- Vocab is 43 tags, within the 30-50 target. Every post got 2-5 canonical tags (/adblocker-trojan, /viz, /advertising, /software-rot are narrow and got 2-3; richer posts got 5)."
